# Acme Corp — Systems Architecture
@diagram|id:acme-systems|type:flow|purpose:Platform-wide service topology for Acme Corp SaaS|direction:TD

# ── External boundary ──────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:external|label:External

@node|id:Browser|label:Web Browser|shape:stadium|group:external
@node|id:MobileApp|label:Mobile App|shape:stadium|group:external
@node|id:ThirdParty|label:Partner API|shape:hexagon|group:external

# ── Edge / ingress ─────────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:edge|label:Edge Layer

@node|id:CDN|label:CloudFront CDN|group:edge
@node|id:WAF|label:WAF / DDoS Shield|group:edge
@node|id:LB|label:ALB Load Balancer|group:edge

@edge|from:Browser|to:CDN|label:HTTPS
@edge|from:MobileApp|to:CDN|label:HTTPS
@edge|from:CDN|to:WAF|label:filtered traffic
@edge|from:WAF|to:LB|label:clean traffic

# ── API gateway & BFF ─────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:gateway|label:API Gateway

@node|id:APIGW|label:Kong API Gateway|group:gateway
@node|id:BFF|label:BFF (Backend for Frontend)|group:gateway
@node|id:RateLimiter|label:Rate Limiter|shape:diamond|group:gateway

@edge|from:LB|to:APIGW|label:routes
@edge|from:APIGW|to:RateLimiter|label:checks quota
@edge|from:APIGW|to:BFF|label:forwards

# ── Core services ──────────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:core|label:Core Services

@node|id:UserSvc|label:User Service|group:core
@node|id:AuthSvc|label:Auth Service|group:core
@node|id:BillingSvc|label:Billing Service|group:core
@node|id:NotifySvc|label:Notification Service|group:core
@node|id:SearchSvc|label:Search Service|group:core

@edge|from:BFF|to:UserSvc|label:gRPC
@edge|from:BFF|to:AuthSvc|label:gRPC
@edge|from:BFF|to:BillingSvc|label:gRPC
@edge|from:BFF|to:SearchSvc|label:gRPC
@edge|from:UserSvc|to:NotifySvc|label:async event
@edge|from:BillingSvc|to:NotifySvc|label:async event
@edge|from:ThirdParty|to:APIGW|label:webhook

# ── Async / messaging ─────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:messaging|label:Event Bus

@node|id:Kafka|label:Kafka Cluster|shape:hexagon|group:messaging
@node|id:DLQ|label:Dead Letter Queue|shape:database|group:messaging

@edge|from:UserSvc|to:Kafka|label:user.events
@edge|from:BillingSvc|to:Kafka|label:payment.events
@edge|from:Kafka|to:NotifySvc|label:consumes
@edge|from:Kafka|to:DLQ|label:failed messages|style:dashed

# ── Data layer ─────────────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:data|label:Data Layer

@node|id:UserDB|label:Users Postgres|shape:database|group:data
@node|id:BillingDB|label:Billing Postgres|shape:database|group:data
@node|id:Redis|label:Redis Cache|shape:database|group:data
@node|id:Elastic|label:Elasticsearch|shape:database|group:data
@node|id:S3|label:S3 Object Store|shape:database|group:data

@edge|from:UserSvc|to:UserDB|label:reads/writes
@edge|from:BillingSvc|to:BillingDB|label:reads/writes
@edge|from:AuthSvc|to:Redis|label:session cache
@edge|from:SearchSvc|to:Elastic|label:queries
@edge|from:NotifySvc|to:S3|label:stores templates

# ── Observability ──────────────────────────────────────────
@group|id:observability|label:Observability

@node|id:Prometheus|label:Prometheus|group:observability
@node|id:Grafana|label:Grafana Dashboards|group:observability
@node|id:Jaeger|label:Jaeger Tracing|group:observability
@node|id:PagerDuty|label:PagerDuty|shape:hexagon|group:observability

@edge|from:Prometheus|to:Grafana|label:metrics
@edge|from:Grafana|to:PagerDuty|label:alerts
@edge|from:Jaeger|to:Grafana|label:trace links

# ── Views ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
@view|id:request-path|filter:tags:core|label:Request Path Only
@view|id:data-only|includes:data|label:Data Stores
@view|id:external-facing|includes:external,edge,gateway|label:External-Facing

# ── Gotchas & decisions ────────────────────────────────────
@gotcha|issue:Kafka consumer lag|detail:Notification service can fall behind during billing runs; lag > 10 min triggers PagerDuty|fix:Scale notification consumer group; add backpressure on billing batch size
@gotcha|issue:CDN cache invalidation|detail:Static assets cached for 24 h; stale JS after deploys causes 404s on lazy-loaded chunks|fix:Content-hash filenames + versioned deploy paths
@gotcha|issue:Rate limiter bypass|detail:Internal services calling Kong bypass rate limits via service mesh; a runaway retry loop can saturate downstream|fix:Mesh-level circuit breakers + per-service quotas

@decision|id:ADR-012|title:Kong over AWS API Gateway|status:accepted|reason:Need plugin ecosystem for custom auth + request transforms; AWS APIGW lacks gRPC transcoding
@decision|id:ADR-015|title:Kafka over SQS for eventing|status:accepted|reason:Need ordering guarantees and replay capability for billing audit trail

@component|name:Kong API Gateway|file:infra/kong/kong.yaml|does:Routes external traffic, enforces auth, rate limits, request transforms
@component|name:User Service|file:services/user-svc/main.go|does:CRUD for user accounts, emits user.events to Kafka
@component|name:Billing Service|file:services/billing-svc/main.go|does:Subscription management, payment processing via Stripe

@config|param:kafka.replication.factor|value:3|note:Minimum for production durability
@config|param:redis.maxmemory-policy|value:allkeys-lru|note:Evict least-recently-used when cache full
@config|param:cdn.default-ttl|value:86400|note:24 h; override per-route for API responses

@entry|use-case:Web login flow|command:Browser -> CDN -> WAF -> LB -> APIGW -> AuthSvc -> Redis
@entry|use-case:Webhook ingestion|command:ThirdParty -> APIGW -> BillingSvc -> Kafka

@note|context:scaling|text:User and Billing services auto-scale 2-8 pods based on CPU; Search is memory-bound and scales on JVM heap
